AERENQUEST GAMES
================
Game ideas for the Sunrice root visualization project.
Engine: VTK/vedo, Python, precomputed aerenchyme meshes + wind-field particles.
Leaderboard: GitHub API → rfernandez/sunrice-leaderboard (leaderboard.json)

Score types
-----------
  time_asc    : lower time is better  (Le Messager, Circuit, Cross, Root Dive, Savior, Infection)
  points_desc : higher count is better (Catch the Pillars, Membrane Surfer, Aero-Census)

Legend  [ ] to do  [~] in progress  [x] done


══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 INFRASTRUCTURE
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[ ] Leaderboard — GitHub API client
      marvel_view/leaderboard/models.py   — ScoreEntry dataclass
      marvel_view/leaderboard/client.py   — read/write leaderboard.json via GitHub API
                                            local SQLite fallback when offline
                                            flush pending on next successful submit
      marvel_view/leaderboard/ui.py       — vedo Text2D overlay (top-10 display)
                                            NameEntry widget (VTK keyboard capture)
      SUNRICE_LB_TOKEN env var            — PAT with contents:write on sunrice-leaderboard repo
      SUNRICE_LB_REPO  env var            — default: rfernandez/sunrice-leaderboard

[ ] GitHub repo setup
      Create rfernandez/sunrice-leaderboard (private or public)
      Commit an initial empty leaderboard.json: {"games": {}}
      Generate a fine-grained PAT: Contents → Read and Write on that repo only
      Set SUNRICE_LB_TOKEN on each machine (laptop + phenodrone + any future machine)
      Document in repo README how to set the token

[ ] Game base class
      marvel_view/scripts/games/base_game.py
      Abstract interface: start() tick(dt) end() → ScoreEntry
      Timer HUD (top-center), score HUD (top-right)
      Integrates with the master 16ms scheduler in app.py


══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 GAMES — USER IDEAS
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[ ] LE MESSAGER  (game_id: le_messager)
      Score type  : time_asc
      Data needed : any dataset with aerenchyme + cortex
      Mechanic
        - Timer starts immediately (displayed top-center)
        - Player = metallic olive-green particle (specular, mirror-like)
        - Opening : close-up of a random "source" cell (cortex mesh bounce)
                    speech bubble: "J'ai un message à délivrer, qui peut m'aider ?"
                    player insight: "J'arrive !"
        - Navigation arrow (HUD) points toward source cell from camera center
        - Player navigates to source cell in full tissue mesh
        - Source cell close-up: "Voici le message." / "De quoi s'agit-il ?"
                                 cell blushes (pink flush), tiny arc, silly face
                                 "C'est un secret !"
        - Navigation arrow now points toward target cell
        - Player navigates to target cell
        - Target cell close-up: "Merci beaucoup ! Au revoir !"  → timer stops
        - Name entry → leaderboard submit
      Implementation notes
        - Source cell: random CC accessible from exterior (connected_components.interior_mask)
        - Target cell: different random accessible CC
        - Arrow HUD: project cell centroid to screen, draw 2D direction arrow
        - Speech bubbles: vedo Text2D overlay with auto-hide timer

[ ] CROSS THE BEAST  (game_id: cross_the_beast)
      Score type  : time_asc
      Data needed : dataset with pillars + trackways visible
      Mechanic
        - Mode: trackways + pillars, stele (central cylinder) is blocked/opaque
        - Go from one root end to the other through cortex only
        - Must NOT touch a pillar or a trackway (collision sphere around player)
        - On touch: restart from entry point (no penalty time, just restart pos)
        - Timer stops when player reaches the far end of the root
        - Name entry → leaderboard
      Implementation notes
        - Collision: distance from camera pos to each pillar/trackway actor centroid < threshold
        - Entry/exit: bounding box extremes along root axis (Z or longest axis)

[ ] CATCH THE PILLARS  (game_id: catch_pillars)
      Score type  : points_desc
      Data needed : any dataset with pillar actors
      Mechanic
        - Mode: Lames view
        - 2-minute countdown (HUD top-left)
        - Catch a pillar by flying within proximity radius
        - On catch: actor.SetVisibility(0), score += 1 (displayed top-right)
        - After 2 min: name entry → leaderboard
      Implementation notes
        - Simplest game to implement — proximity check on pillar actors each tick
        - Proximity radius ~ 5% of scene diagonal
        - Caught count persists even if player revisits the area

[ ] CIRCUIT  (game_id: circuit)
      Score type  : time_asc  (ranked by average speed = total_dist / elapsed_time)
      Data needed : any dataset with cortex mesh
      Mechanic
        - N random control points drawn inside cortex mesh (default N=8)
        - Each materialised as a translucent ring (opacity 0.3) orthogonal to
          the line from previous → next waypoint
        - Current target ring highlighted (slightly more opaque / glowing)
        - Player must fly through each ring in sequence
        - Passing a ring: distance from camera to ring center < ring radius
          AND camera crossed the ring plane (dot product sign change)
        - Timer starts at ring 1, stops when ring N is passed
        - Leaderboard key: average speed (voxels/s) OR elapsed time
        - Name entry → leaderboard
      Implementation notes
        - Rings: vtkDiskSource with inner_radius = outer_radius * 0.9, thin disk
        - Random points: sample cortex mesh surface, push inward by normal * offset
        - Ring orientation: normal = direction to next waypoint

[ ] THE SAVIOR  (game_id: the_savior)  ← CHEF D'ŒUVRE — deferred until long-root data available
      Score type  : time_asc  (leaderboard tracks completions, i.e. people who made it)
      Data needed : LONG root dataset (full root length, many aerenchyme cavities)
      Music       : Vivaldi — L'Estate (Summer) from Le Quattro Stagioni  ← check license
      Mechanic
        - Opening cinematic:
            Far end of root: cell speech bubble "Je suis une cellule de la pointe,
            la racine est inondée, j'ai besoin d'oxygène, au secours !"
            Player particle (blue-white, mirror brilliant): "Je suis une molécule
            d'oxygène, je vais te sauver !"
        - Control: YAW + PITCH + ROLL only — no speed control (constant forward velocity)
        - Vivaldi starts, player dives into root from crown end
        - HUD bar 1: SANTÉ de la cellule (decreases over time, orange/red)
        - HUD bar 2: DISTANCE à la cellule (decreases as player advances)
        - Mid-sequence drama:
            Cell: "J'étouffe... arg !"
            Tissue turns orange/red
            Speed increases
        - Win condition: reach the target cell before health bar empties
        - End: "Merci !! Tu m'as sauvée !" → timer stops → leaderboard (win only)
        - Lose condition: health bar empty → "..." → fade to red → restart offer
      Implementation notes
        - Speed ramp: linear until drama trigger, then step-up × 1.5
        - Health bar: simple vedo Rectangle actor, shrinks left-to-right
        - Distance bar: similar, shrinks as camera Z approaches target Z
        - Cinematic speech: same Text2D overlay system as Le Messager


══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 GAMES — SUGGESTED EXTRAS
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[ ] ROOT DIVE  (game_id: root_dive)
      Score type  : time_asc
      Mechanic    : Enter through the crown, reach the root tip staying inside
                    aerenchyme channels. Pure speedrun, no obstacles.
                    Timer stops at the tip bounding box edge.
      Simplest game to implement after Catch the Pillars.

[ ] MEMBRANE SURFER  (game_id: membrane_surfer)
      Score type  : points_desc  (distance surfed)
      Mechanic    : Ride the descending water membrane animation (already in engine).
                    Stay within ±3 animation frames of the current membrane front.
                    Falling too far behind or ahead ends the run.
                    Score = how many membrane steps you stayed in sync with.

[ ] AERO-CENSUS  (game_id: aero_census)
      Score type  : points_desc  (% cells identified)
      Mechanic    : Educational. 2-minute timer. Fly through the section and
                    "scan" cell types by proximity (cortex / endodermis /
                    aerenchyme / stele). Each cell type scanned once = +1 point.
                    HUD shows mini map of identified zones.

[ ] INFECTION  (game_id: infection)
      Score type  : time_asc
      Mechanic    : A contamination wave spreads from the crown end (red voxel
                    front advancing at constant speed). Player is a white-cell
                    molecule. Must reach the stele center at the tip before the
                    infection does. Infection wave uses the same membrane
                    animation system but reversed / recolored.


